rComments: one of the best teachers u could find. i have 103 in dawson with him, i wish he teached BXE too!

The best professor I've ever had. He's knowledgable, compassionate, and takes care to ensure every lecture is useful and entertaining. He gives excellent feedback on assignments and provides ample opportunity to revise graded material. Snappy dresser. Loves puns.
Being a science student in his class sucks-- ridicules any scientific idea for a paper in this class. Used to love writing until I took this class!
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Participation matters', 'So many papers']

rComments: In my opinion, Zac has found the perfect balance between friend and professor. Entertaining and relatable, but he still maintains control of the class, which I attribute to how much the students respect him. He's what all the "cool" professors try to be. Grades are earned not given, but his ability to teach and fair grading makes an A attainable.
Excellent lecturer. Turned what could have been an excruciating class into a delight.
Good prof. He kept things like grammar interesting and had a lot of enthusiasm for course material.

Excellent professor! I enjoy his enthusiasm for learning. Very good slides selection of books to read for Mystery novel. However if you do not like reading then you will have a hard time reading 7 novels in one semester Overall this professor is excellent especially for a young one This prof provided lots of help as well. Keep up the AMAZING work!!
Extremely wonderful professor/person. Highly amusing, great power points. Goes on tangents, but always enjoyable. Genuinely loves teaching and discussion. Dresses up for class. Lovely.

Mystery Novels.A lot of reading so if you do not like to read I suggest you don't take this calss. Very interesting. Cool teacher relates to everyday stuff!All in all I suggest you take his class :) Good teacher!

This was a great class, I learned a lot ! Prof Abram is super funny and helpful! He makes every class enjoyable and fun. There are numerous readings , but he picks a wide range so your sure to like most if not all. Not an easy class, but fair!

A really easy class, I managed to make it the most difficult class ever. But he is honestly really easy and super nice! Only issue is that there was 7 novels to read for the class the rest of the work required 2 essays and one final exam. The last written essay is worth more than the final exam. Such a nice teacher though!

Amazing as a teacher. He is very engaging and enthusiastic about mystery. His feedback is extremely helpful and is always available for help outside of class. There's a lot of readings, but the books assigned are great reads. Highly recommend this class with this prof.

Zac is funny and would probably be a cool friend outside of class. He assigns SO much reading, but if you love Mystery Novels you probably won't mind. Not a bird course, but fair. Luscious bears as well.

Learnt so much in his essay writing class. Be sure to go do discussion groups where you learn the grammar portion. Encourages discussion in class. Tests weren't super tricky if you payed attention to his/TA comments in your previous essays. References a lot of elitist/hipster/eccentric/historical points beware!
interesting guy. sweet mustache. wore a bow-tie to the last lecture. bird course.

He's a really good prof. He tries to get everyone interested in his discussions which is hard to do since it's a really boring class. His discussion are actually really interesting and he's pretty funny. Not to mention he's cute (once you get past the beard). If you can take his class !

Great Prof. Very Clear. Very Funny. Managed to make essay writing an exciting class... which is hard to accomplish. He's very helpful and genuinely wants you to succeed. Warning: You will fall in live with him :)
Good prof, very helpful. He enjoys getting everyone involved in discussions. Keeps the class interesting
He was really helpful and is really willing to help you improve your writing. Excellent Prof overall
